# Realtors360 CRM — Cursor Rules
# Source of truth: .claude/agent-playbook.md + AGENTS.md

## MANDATORY — Read Before Every Task
1. Read `.claude/agent-playbook.md` (playbook) and `.claude/quick-reference.md` (checklist)
2. Classify every task BEFORE making changes (task type, tier, affected files)
3. Follow the playbook step by step — no shortcuts, no skipping

## Hard Constraints (violation = automatic revert)
- No `any` type, no `@ts-ignore`, no inline styles
- Server Actions for mutations (src/actions/), API routes for GETs/webhooks only
- RLS required on every new table with realtor_id scoping
- Multi-tenant: use `getAuthenticatedTenantClient()` for ALL user data — never raw admin client
- Every new table MUST have `realtor_id` column with index and RLS policy
- Zod v4 validation on all form/API/webhook inputs
- Never push directly to `main` or `dev` — PRs only
- Never commit `.env.local` — use `scripts/vault.sh`
- No PII in AI prompts (no phone, email, FINTRAC data, tokens)
- CASL consent check before every outbound message
- Verify against actual code, not reports — "code written" ≠ "feature works"

## Architecture
- Next.js 16 App Router + Supabase + TypeScript
- CSS: `lf-*` design system classes from globals.css
- Path alias: `@/` maps to `src/`
- `force-dynamic` on pages with live Supabase data
- `revalidatePath()` after every mutation

## Multi-Tenancy
- `getAuthenticatedTenantClient()` auto-injects `.eq("realtor_id", userId)` on all queries
- Auto-injects realtor_id on inserts — never pass it manually
- Admin users bypass via `createAdminClient()`
- Global tables (exempt): google_tokens, newsletter_templates, workflow_blueprints, knowledge_articles

## Deliverables (every feature change)
- CODING:feature → usecases/<feature>.md BEFORE coding
- CODING:feature/bugfix/refactor → tests written AFTER coding
- Any code change → tests RUN (not just tsc)
- PR must include: classification block, test results, deliverable status

## Git Workflow
- Branch: `<developer>/<description>` from dev
- PR to dev (0 approvals, merge your own)
- PR dev → main (1 approval for release)
- Conventional commits: feat: fix: refactor: docs: test: chore: security:

## Testing
- `npm run typecheck` — TypeScript check
- `npm test` — full test suite (73+ tests)
- `npm run test:quick` — Vitest unit tests
- `npx playwright test` — browser tests
